doctype 5
html(lang="en")
    head
        title Scrum Hub, agile method with GitHub
        include head
    body
        #content
            h1 Welcome to Scrum Hub

            .social-btns
                .fb-like(data-send="false", data-layout="button_count", data-width="450", data-show-faces="false")
                a(href="https://twitter.com/j_sanp", class="twitter-follow-button", data-show-count="false", data-show-screen-name="false") Follow @j_sanp
                a(href="https://twitter.com/share", class="twitter-share-button") Tweet
                a(href="https://github.com/j-san/JTmpl")
                    img(style="position: absolute; top: 0; right: 0; border: 0;",
                        src="http://s3.amazonaws.com/github/ribbons/forkme_right_darkblue_121621.png",
                        alt="Fork me on GitHub")

            ul
                li your code is on 
                    strong GitHub
                li your documentation is on 
                    strong GitHub
                li your issue tracking is on 
                    strong GitHub
                li: strong why don't you manage your Scrum Planning on GitHub ?

            p.center: a.btn.btn-primary(href="/projects/") select a project

            p Manage product backlog, plan sprints and resolve stories.
            p Your data is stored on GitHub database using GitHub API,
                | use all awesome features from GitHub:
            ul
                li links commits to stories
                li get notifications
                li refs to users, projects, issues, ...
                li be social

            p Comming soon: connect you project with Continuous Integration
                | tools such as TravisCI and do Continuous Deployment.

        include ga
        #fb-root
